1
00:00:10,213 --> 00:00:12,177
Suer, what's wrong with you?

2
00:00:13,093 --> 00:00:17,222
Hey, what's gotten into you?
You're not staying over at Nao's place today?

3
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:19,471
- Can you not say that name?
- You don't want to be friends with him anymore?

4
00:00:19,471 --> 00:00:21,440
No. I don't want to be friends anymore.

5
00:00:21,710 --> 00:00:25,217
- Move. Nao's coming.
- It's not a big deal. We're just here to eat. Come on.

6
00:00:25,271 --> 00:00:27,271
- Hey, where are you going, Field?
- We'll be late.

7
00:00:27,368 --> 00:00:28,684
Wait, Suer.

8
00:00:28,942 --> 00:00:31,528
- What?
- Is there something you want to tell me?

9
00:00:31,786 --> 00:00:36,142
You can keep a secret, right?
Then I'll tell you my secret on Saturday.

10
00:00:36,417 --> 00:00:37,800
I'm worried about you.

11
00:00:37,928 --> 00:00:40,462
Hey, there's definitely more to this.

12
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:46,488
Hey.

13
00:00:47,537 --> 00:00:48,893
It suddenly started raining.

14
00:00:49,844 --> 00:00:50,848
Yeah.

15
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:52,631
It looked gloomy since this morning.

16
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,528
And it's freaking cold (Nao )too.

17
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,960
- Nao?
- Yeah, cold.

18
00:00:57,155 --> 00:00:58,142
Right.

19
00:00:58,740 --> 00:00:59,888
Really Nao.

20
00:01:02,204 --> 00:01:04,128
What's with you? Why are you repeating everything I say?

21
00:01:06,102 --> 00:01:08,540
Why? Are you the only one allowed to say "Nao" (cold)?

22
00:01:10,435 --> 00:01:11,928
No.

23
00:01:12,635 --> 00:01:14,808
But it's the rainy season now, right?

24
00:01:15,306 --> 00:01:17,373
Yeah, it's the rainy season.

25
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:20,088
It's Duennao (Winter) season.

26
00:01:20,937 --> 00:01:22,400
It's the rainy season.

27
00:01:22,586 --> 00:01:25,724
No. I want it to be Duennao (Winter) season.

28
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:28,480
Shit.

29
00:01:32,431 --> 00:01:33,844
Wait a second.

30
00:01:33,982 --> 00:01:37,777
Room Nine just walked by. Why are you reacting so hard?

31
00:01:38,657 --> 00:01:40,880
Got something to tell me, Suer?

32
00:01:41,168 --> 00:01:41,860
What?

33
00:01:42,302 --> 00:01:45,546
Wow, look at those lovesick eyes.

34
00:01:46,071 --> 00:01:47,382
Who are you looking at?

35
00:01:49,337 --> 00:01:51,773
No one. What are you talking about, Mick?

36
00:01:52,026 --> 00:01:53,933
- Shut up.
- Aha!

37
00:02:02,297 --> 00:02:03,151
Field.

38
00:02:05,253 --> 00:02:06,666
What's wrong with our friend lately?

39
00:02:07,497 --> 00:02:09,520
One minute he's annoyed, the next he's smiling.

40
00:02:09,951 --> 00:02:11,764
Yeah, I've noticed.

41
00:02:11,946 --> 00:02:13,382
I'm starting to get scared.

42
00:02:13,546 --> 00:02:15,968
Damn, I really want to change seats.

43
00:02:16,182 --> 00:02:17,671
Want to sit next to me?

44
00:02:22,622 --> 00:02:24,053
I think he's gone crazy.

45
00:02:31,057 --> 00:02:33,453
Class dismissed. You can all go home now.

46
00:02:33,764 --> 00:02:35,711
Thank youuu.

47
00:02:35,884 --> 00:02:37,666
Finally.

48
00:02:41,217 --> 00:02:42,844
What are you doing after this?

49
00:02:43,137 --> 00:02:44,444
Going home.

50
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:45,773
Hey, Suer.

51
00:02:46,191 --> 00:02:48,942
- We're going to the game café. Wanna come?
- Yea.

52
00:02:50,257 --> 00:02:51,435
The game café?

53
00:02:51,995 --> 00:02:54,848
Come with us. You can't practice today anyway.

54
00:02:55,084 --> 00:02:57,493
The field's completely soaked.

55
00:02:58,017 --> 00:03:01,862
- Sure.
- Let's go play some games, buddy.

56
00:03:02,048 --> 00:03:03,937
Alright.
Today...

57
00:03:04,217 --> 00:03:06,022
Sword fighting game?

58
00:03:06,293 --> 00:03:07,173
Dota.

59
00:03:11,022 --> 00:03:15,204
- No idea. What should we play?
- I don't feel like shooters today. I wanna play something...

60
00:03:15,644 --> 00:03:17,844
- Build houses? Minecraft?
- Let Suer choose.

61
00:03:18,155 --> 00:03:19,271
Sure, Suer.

62
00:03:19,715 --> 00:03:20,982
What do you want to play, Suer?

63
00:03:29,502 --> 00:03:30,777
Where'd you get that gun from?

64
00:03:33,448 --> 00:03:34,177
I'm heading home.

65
00:03:34,391 --> 00:03:36,751
Huh? You just got here.

66
00:03:37,048 --> 00:03:38,360
What's wrong with you?

67
00:03:39,568 --> 00:03:41,195
I'm... sad.

68
00:03:41,742 --> 00:03:43,928
Sad about what? You were fine a second ago.

69
00:03:45,533 --> 00:03:46,768
Just go.

70
00:03:47,217 --> 00:03:50,488
- Hey, come play with us.
- Get home safe.

71
00:03:51,742 --> 00:03:52,600
- Suer.
- Shit!

72
00:03:53,502 --> 00:03:55,573
Damn it! Why the hell are you yelling, idiot?

73
00:03:56,551 --> 00:03:57,728
So, are you going home today?

74
00:04:00,311 --> 00:04:02,444
- Why are you asking me?
- I'm just asking.

75
00:04:02,586 --> 00:04:04,644
- Then why ask me?
- So I can know.

76
00:04:04,724 --> 00:04:06,435
Ask someone else to hang out.

77
00:04:08,564 --> 00:04:09,324
Who?

78
00:04:10,217 --> 00:04:11,088
I don't know.

79
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:12,355
See ya.

80
00:04:21,555 --> 00:04:24,160
What the hell is wrong with you, Suer? Damn it.

81
00:06:07,235 --> 00:06:08,502
Whoa.

82
00:06:10,653 --> 00:06:12,302
What the hell is this lump?

83
00:06:13,035 --> 00:06:14,275
What is this?

84
00:06:17,924 --> 00:06:18,706
Hey.

85
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:20,760
What the hell are you doing?

86
00:06:23,875 --> 00:06:25,213
What is he spacing out about?

87
00:06:30,306 --> 00:06:32,026
What the hell are you guys doing?

88
00:06:32,502 --> 00:06:35,653
What's gotten into you guys?

89
00:06:35,724 --> 00:06:37,902
Come on, we're just messing around.

90
00:06:40,577 --> 00:06:42,422
- Hey, sorry.
- Did you buy alcohol?

91
00:06:44,822 --> 00:06:45,706
I bought milk.

92
00:06:46,751 --> 00:06:48,515
Do you drink milk when you're sad or something?

93
00:06:48,924 --> 00:06:51,893
Why would I drink alcohol?
I'll drink when I'm old enough.

94
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:55,982
Anyway.

95
00:06:56,373 --> 00:06:58,951
What are you sad about? I noticed it at the game café.

96
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:03,764
You know, Nao saw you looking sad.
He was totally confused.

97
00:07:04,937 --> 00:07:07,000
And what did you tell Nao?

98
00:07:07,328 --> 00:07:09,293
I just told him you were sad.

99
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:10,817
What?

100
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:11,871
Well...

101
00:07:12,337 --> 00:07:13,346
Why?

102
00:07:13,444 --> 00:07:16,693
You said you were sad,
so that's what I told him.

103
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:28,940
You...

104
00:07:30,026 --> 00:07:32,751
- You told him that?
- Yeah, of course.

105
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:36,862
Why? So are you finally gonna tell us why you're sad or what?

106
00:07:37,151 --> 00:07:38,844
Otherwise, I'm not asking anymore.

107
00:07:49,697 --> 00:07:50,791
If...

108
00:07:51,364 --> 00:07:52,751
I tell you guys...

109
00:07:54,666 --> 00:07:56,737
you better keep it a secret.

110
00:07:57,573 --> 00:07:58,386
Mm.

111
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,311
I think...

112
00:08:04,808 --> 00:08:06,897
I like Nao.

113
00:08:09,177 --> 00:08:09,995
What?

114
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:13,182
Can you say that again?

115
00:08:13,497 --> 00:08:15,733
Yeah, I like Nao.

116
00:08:17,568 --> 00:08:19,844
Nao, not Nue?

117
00:08:25,071 --> 00:08:25,915
Why though?

118
00:08:26,688 --> 00:08:27,740
"Why" what?

119
00:08:29,506 --> 00:08:30,906
Why do you like him? Just curious.

120
00:08:35,835 --> 00:08:37,026
I don't know.

121
00:08:38,195 --> 00:08:39,057
I...

122
00:08:39,902 --> 00:08:41,671
just realized one day that I liked him.

123
00:08:43,737 --> 00:08:45,711
That's what I wanted to tell you guys today.

124
00:08:46,853 --> 00:08:47,942
What do you think?

125
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:50,706
What should I do next?

126
00:08:52,471 --> 00:08:56,022
Are you seriously telling me
that you've been sitting there all sad...

127
00:08:56,191 --> 00:08:57,671
because you already got rejected?

128
00:08:57,862 --> 00:08:59,866
- Heh. Not yet.
- Huh?

129
00:09:00,742 --> 00:09:02,506
Then what are you sad about?

130
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:05,946
Well...

131
00:09:07,977 --> 00:09:10,102
- I felt hurt.
- Hurt?

132
00:09:12,595 --> 00:09:14,928
He smiled at someone else. I didn't like it.

133
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:18,044
Oh my god, what is this?

134
00:09:18,164 --> 00:09:20,942
My friend has a childish side like this?

135
00:09:21,191 --> 00:09:24,946
You're ridiculously sensitive.
I never knew you were like this when you liked someone.

136
00:09:28,728 --> 00:09:29,786
What about you guys?

137
00:09:30,511 --> 00:09:32,124
What do you think I should do?

138
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,000
Suer.

139
00:09:38,506 --> 00:09:40,302
Hey, wake up.

140
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:47,644
- Suer.
- Shit.

141
00:09:47,746 --> 00:09:51,120
- Why are you yelling?
- Wake up. We've got studying to do.

142
00:09:51,324 --> 00:09:53,564
- Study what?
- For the exams.

143
00:09:54,937 --> 00:09:55,782
Exams?

144
00:09:57,226 --> 00:09:58,431
What exams?

145
00:09:58,751 --> 00:10:00,782
Midterms. Don't tell me you forgot.

146
00:10:02,275 --> 00:10:04,684
Whatever.

147
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:11,137
Do you think it'd be a good idea if we went to study at Nao's house?

148
00:10:17,675 --> 00:10:19,840
- Would it?
- Look at you, getting up that fast.

149
00:10:20,035 --> 00:10:24,542
Of course it would. Don't you want to see what Duennao is like when he studies?

150
00:10:28,364 --> 00:10:29,746
What do you think?

151
00:10:30,177 --> 00:10:32,284
If I were the one tutoring Duennao...

152
00:10:33,004 --> 00:10:34,275
wouldn't I look cool?

153
00:10:34,497 --> 00:10:38,342
- Like a smart guy.
- Hah, a smart guy?

154
00:10:38,608 --> 00:10:42,786
What smart guy? You haven't paid attention in class at all this semester.

155
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:48,004
You've been bombing every graded test.
How are you supposed to be a smart guy?

156
00:10:49,604 --> 00:10:50,893
I think...

157
00:10:51,097 --> 00:10:53,751
you guys... seriously...

158
00:10:54,435 --> 00:10:55,888
should call me Tiger instead.

159
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,660
- Why?
- Yeah.

160
00:10:59,168 --> 00:11:02,208
We've been calling you Suer since kindergarten.

161
00:11:03,253 --> 00:11:04,417
Nah.

162
00:11:04,626 --> 00:11:06,453
Tiger is better because...

163
00:11:06,537 --> 00:11:09,560
Duennao is the only one who gets to call me Suer.

164
00:11:09,608 --> 00:11:11,577
Oh, come on.

165
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,982
I don't even know what to say anymore.

166
00:11:20,684 --> 00:11:24,773
So, are we going to study or not?
Why don't you call and see if he's free first?

167
00:11:25,570 --> 00:11:27,542
- Me?
- Who else?

168
00:11:27,586 --> 00:11:28,737
Of course it's you.

169
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:44,604
Sup?

170
00:11:46,657 --> 00:11:48,848
Uh... you...

171
00:11:49,044 --> 00:11:50,244
interested in studying together?

172
00:11:50,728 --> 00:11:51,835
For midterms?

173
00:11:52,386 --> 00:11:55,462
Yeah. Dan's gonna tutor me this afternoon.

174
00:11:56,706 --> 00:11:58,800
- Let me join too.
- Sure.

175
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:00,991
And Mick...

176
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:06,582
- and Field too. Is that okay?
- Yeah, sure. My friends are coming too. Apo and Tul.

177
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:08,355
Yes!

178
00:12:08,893 --> 00:12:09,791
See you then.

179
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:19,020
- What the hell are you waiting for?
- A shower.

180
00:12:19,271 --> 00:12:23,293
Wow. A minute ago, you didn't even want to get out of bed.

181
00:12:26,742 --> 00:12:29,417
Whoa.

182
00:12:30,004 --> 00:12:32,071
This place has such a nice vibe.

183
00:12:35,395 --> 00:12:36,480
There's a garden too.

184
00:12:37,035 --> 00:12:40,031
Yeah, of course. It's Dan's garden.

185
00:12:43,866 --> 00:12:46,306
By the way, where's Nue?

186
00:12:46,573 --> 00:12:47,746
Isn't he studying with us?

187
00:12:48,013 --> 00:12:50,031
Dan went to the market with mom. He'll be back soon.

188
00:13:01,226 --> 00:13:03,324
Hey, Nao. Can I use the bathroom?

189
00:13:04,773 --> 00:13:07,408
The bathroom? It's over there. Just go downstairs and you'll find it.

190
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:08,964
Okay.

191
00:13:10,288 --> 00:13:14,155
Actually, I'll go too. I kinda need to use it.

192
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:19,866
- There's only one bathroom.
- That's fine. I'll wait downstairs.

193
00:13:25,204 --> 00:13:26,546
Why are they in such a hurry?

194
00:13:30,013 --> 00:13:31,580
- Suer.
- Huh?

195
00:13:32,213 --> 00:13:33,431
Are you feeling better now?

196
00:13:34,168 --> 00:13:34,871
What?

197
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:37,328
You can tell me if something's bothering you.

198
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,533
- Are you okay?
- Hey, I'm gonna use the bathroom for a sec.

199
00:13:46,622 --> 00:13:48,453
Dude, Field's already in there.

200
00:13:50,786 --> 00:13:52,120
Does he really have to go that badly?

201
00:13:55,146 --> 00:13:56,524
What the hell are you guys doing?

202
00:13:56,915 --> 00:13:59,782
So you could be alone with Nao.

203
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:03,840
The two of us went through all for you, you know.

204
00:14:04,395 --> 00:14:06,964
Thanks a lot, assholes. You were messing with me more than helping.

205
00:14:07,315 --> 00:14:09,546
And now that you're out here, won't Nao get suspicious?

206
00:14:10,595 --> 00:14:12,373
Oh, right. Didn't think of that.

207
00:14:14,337 --> 00:14:16,604
Hey, Nao's coming.

208
00:14:17,275 --> 00:14:18,048
Shit.

209
00:14:21,964 --> 00:14:22,857
Where's Suer?

210
00:14:23,275 --> 00:14:26,528
- He's in the bathroom. Guess he has diarrhea.
- Yeah, yeah.

211
00:14:27,497 --> 00:14:30,546
I figured. I saw him rushing downstairs.

212
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,031
You assholes.

213
00:14:42,942 --> 00:14:43,986
What the hell are you laughing at?

214
00:14:44,644 --> 00:14:48,020
My photo. It's freaking hilarious.

215
00:14:48,168 --> 00:14:50,862
- Let me see.
- No way. It's an embarrassing shot.

216
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:53,888
How can I show you? I look ridiculous in it.

217
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:55,111
Just a little bit.

218
00:14:55,306 --> 00:14:56,955
I'll send it to you later.

219
00:15:04,337 --> 00:15:05,791
Mm. Electrolytes.

220
00:15:08,093 --> 00:15:09,582
Didn't you have diarrhea?

221
00:15:10,662 --> 00:15:12,013
Oh.

222
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,715
Thank you.

223
00:15:14,408 --> 00:15:15,133
Yeah.

224
00:15:29,884 --> 00:15:31,100
You're so fast at math.

225
00:15:31,395 --> 00:15:32,511
Whoa, shit.

226
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,342
Why'd you get startled?

227
00:15:37,435 --> 00:15:38,657
I was just asking.

228
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:40,506
How are you so fast at math?

229
00:15:41,004 --> 00:15:42,226
Got any tricks?

230
00:15:42,662 --> 00:15:44,524
I don't know. It just comes naturally.

231
00:15:45,862 --> 00:15:47,280
Such a smart-person answer.

232
00:15:52,591 --> 00:15:54,702
- Just do it.
- Fine, I'll do it.

233
00:16:00,582 --> 00:16:03,688
What kind of multiplication is that? How did you even make it through middle school?

234
00:16:03,866 --> 00:16:06,124
Hey, everyone makes mistakes sometimes.

235
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,013
I'm not a calculator, you know.

236
00:16:09,866 --> 00:16:11,968
I'm not studying with you anymore. All you do is roast me.

237
00:16:12,537 --> 00:16:13,946
Can you blame me?

238
00:16:15,448 --> 00:16:17,444
Yelling at me isn't gonna make me smarter.

239
00:16:17,884 --> 00:16:19,057
You could just talk nicely to me.

240
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,626
Come on, Tul.

241
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,546
He's basically a kid.

242
00:16:27,742 --> 00:16:30,342
He only listens when the teacher speaks gently.

243
00:16:30,657 --> 00:16:35,106
Whether I yell or not, look at him.
Think he's listening? Who's he texting anyway? Some girl?

244
00:16:35,213 --> 00:16:36,133
Hey.

245
00:16:36,648 --> 00:16:37,764
Hey, Mick.

246
00:16:38,977 --> 00:16:41,231
Don't tell me it's little Yayee.

247
00:16:41,746 --> 00:16:44,822
Damn, he's serious.

248
00:16:47,460 --> 00:16:48,640
They'll break up soon enough.

249
00:16:50,431 --> 00:16:52,097
Hey, that's way too mean.

250
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:55,177
Hmph. I'm sulking now.

251
00:16:55,946 --> 00:16:57,977
Don't think it'll be easy to make it up to me,

252
00:16:58,186 --> 00:17:00,386
Mr. Tula.

253
00:17:00,662 --> 00:17:02,213
Annoying.

254
00:17:09,608 --> 00:17:10,728
Want to go sit with Field?

255
00:17:11,773 --> 00:17:12,822
Nah.

256
00:17:16,715 --> 00:17:19,293
What are you doing, Dan? Still not asleep?

257
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:21,813
I can't sleep.

258
00:17:23,497 --> 00:17:24,617
Worried about something?

259
00:17:25,311 --> 00:17:26,151
Yeah.

260
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,684
What about? Midterms?

261
00:17:30,857 --> 00:17:32,540
That doesn't seem like something you'd worry about.

262
00:17:36,022 --> 00:17:36,977
Sorry.

263
00:17:37,088 --> 00:17:39,266
I didn't want you to worry too.

264
00:17:40,026 --> 00:17:42,951
But sooner or later, we're going to have to face it.

265
00:17:45,226 --> 00:17:46,688
You mean...

266
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,688
about Chat?

267
00:17:50,831 --> 00:17:52,320
Don't worry.

268
00:17:52,475 --> 00:17:54,768
I'll protect you myself.

269
00:18:00,071 --> 00:18:01,524
Come on, let's sleep.

270
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,791
Sweet dreams, kiddo.

271
00:18:29,928 --> 00:18:32,755
Kiddo? You were only born nine minutes earlier.

272
00:18:32,835 --> 00:18:34,102
Do you even have the right to say that?

273
00:18:35,715 --> 00:18:37,480
Little kid.

274
00:18:49,488 --> 00:18:51,240
Don't put too much pressure on yourself, Dan.

275
00:18:52,137 --> 00:18:53,688
I know you're the type to do that.

276
00:18:54,155 --> 00:18:56,266
Because you're the oldest sibling in the family.

277
00:18:57,600 --> 00:19:00,568
This is something I want to do anyway. It's okay.

278
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:06,542
Then I'll study hard...

279
00:19:06,893 --> 00:19:09,080
so you won't have to work so hard. Okay?

280
00:19:10,088 --> 00:19:12,146
Thanks, but it's okay.

281
00:19:12,453 --> 00:19:14,413
Just do what you want to do.

282
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:18,244
Neither Mom nor I have ever stopped you from doing what you want.

283
00:19:18,662 --> 00:19:21,675
So don't put too much pressure on yourself.

284
00:19:25,968 --> 00:19:26,928
Mm.

285
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:30,728
- Sweet dreams.
- Sweet dreams to you too.

286
00:19:50,782 --> 00:19:52,862
Hey, Suer. Feeling better?

287
00:19:55,297 --> 00:19:56,164
Hm?

288
00:19:57,155 --> 00:19:57,813
Hm?

289
00:19:57,853 --> 00:19:59,680
Your diarrhea, remember?

290
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:04,955
Oh, right. Yeah, my stomach still hurts.

291
00:20:05,542 --> 00:20:07,026
That bad?

292
00:20:08,422 --> 00:20:11,653
Should you go to the hospital?
You've got an exam tomorrow. Are you okay?

293
00:20:16,848 --> 00:20:17,973
What are you smiling about?

294
00:20:19,804 --> 00:20:20,737
Nothing.

295
00:20:21,915 --> 00:20:24,942
No need to see a doctor. Some rest should do it.

296
00:20:25,502 --> 00:20:26,555
Okay.

297
00:20:26,906 --> 00:20:29,693
Then I'll have my mom make you some bland food, okay?

298
00:20:31,488 --> 00:20:32,666
I'll be right back.

299
00:20:49,635 --> 00:20:52,737
Mm. Electrolytes.
You'll recover faster.

300
00:20:54,537 --> 00:20:56,022
Thank you.

301
00:21:06,635 --> 00:21:07,684
Hey.

302
00:21:08,644 --> 00:21:09,635
Are you okay?

303
00:21:12,191 --> 00:21:13,133
Yeah.

304
00:21:16,693 --> 00:21:18,035
Can I talk to you about something?

305
00:21:25,853 --> 00:21:26,915
You know...

306
00:21:29,604 --> 00:21:32,871
Do you remember that guy named Chat I told you about?

307
00:21:39,213 --> 00:21:41,017
There's actually more to it than that.

308
00:21:43,222 --> 00:21:46,342
When I said we're not living together anymore...

309
00:21:46,586 --> 00:21:48,733
the truth is, he's in prison now.

310
00:21:50,408 --> 00:21:52,013
He got convicted of robbery.

311
00:21:53,155 --> 00:21:54,768
And when he was living with us...

312
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:59,480
- He'd come home drunk and abuse us.
- Abuse you?

313
00:22:00,351 --> 00:22:01,924
Aunt Maew and Nue too?

314
00:22:09,377 --> 00:22:11,826
And now...

315
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:15,271
he's about to get out of prison.

316
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:17,968
I'm scared that...

317
00:22:18,740 --> 00:22:20,484
if you keep staying here...

318
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:23,911
you might end up in danger too.

319
00:22:26,137 --> 00:22:27,217
I'll handle it myself.

320
00:22:35,573 --> 00:22:36,951
What are you worried about?

321
00:22:37,511 --> 00:22:38,982
Did you forget what I told you?

322
00:22:42,488 --> 00:22:43,595
Yeah.

323
00:22:44,688 --> 00:22:45,391
Well...

324
00:22:46,417 --> 00:22:47,946
you're in the mafia.

325
00:22:50,671 --> 00:22:51,231
But...

326
00:22:52,222 --> 00:22:55,880
I don't want anyone else getting dragged into this.

327
00:22:58,648 --> 00:23:00,013
It's fine.

328
00:23:00,377 --> 00:23:01,860
It's nothing serious.

329
00:23:02,346 --> 00:23:03,820
I'll take care of it.

330
00:23:13,053 --> 00:23:14,475
But...

331
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,306
Think of it as repayment.

332
00:23:18,746 --> 00:23:20,288
For taking care of me.

333
00:23:21,653 --> 00:23:23,840
This is such a small thing.

334
00:23:24,342 --> 00:23:25,964
It's just one person.

335
00:23:26,537 --> 00:23:27,888
What can he really do?

336
00:23:27,995 --> 00:23:28,604
Hm?

337
00:23:33,142 --> 00:23:33,853
Yeah.

338
00:23:33,937 --> 00:23:35,177
So...

339
00:23:35,795 --> 00:23:36,813
Don't stress about it.

340
00:23:37,306 --> 00:23:38,857
I'll handle everything.

341
00:23:39,453 --> 00:23:40,391
Okay?

342
00:23:42,195 --> 00:23:43,293
Yeah.

343
00:23:46,893 --> 00:23:48,857
Still, thanks a lot.

344
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,706
Get some more rest.

345
00:24:10,551 --> 00:24:13,733
- This one's delicious.
- Thank you.

346
00:24:14,262 --> 00:24:15,000
Thank you.

347
00:24:15,084 --> 00:24:16,755
I put a lot of effort into it.

348
00:24:18,146 --> 00:24:20,537
- There's so much food.
- Yeah.

349
00:24:23,017 --> 00:24:24,475
This curry is really rich.

350
00:24:24,666 --> 00:24:26,115
Thank you.

351
00:24:27,595 --> 00:24:31,422
Tiger, aren't you sick? Why don't you sleep in a bed?

352
00:24:31,653 --> 00:24:33,848
You won't be comfortable on the couch.

353
00:24:34,608 --> 00:24:35,875
Dan, come sleep with me.

354
00:24:36,462 --> 00:24:39,568
Uh, I don't want to trouble anyone.

355
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:43,546
I'm already feeling much better.

356
00:24:44,013 --> 00:24:46,315
I can just sleep on the couch.

357
00:24:46,773 --> 00:24:49,582
It's no trouble at all. Rest until you're fully recovered, okay?

358
00:24:50,613 --> 00:24:51,591
Hm?

359
00:24:51,977 --> 00:24:54,457
- What do Duen and Dan think?
- I'm okay with it.

360
00:24:54,702 --> 00:24:58,217
- Whatever you want, Mom.
- Great, you haven't slept with me in ages.

361
00:24:58,546 --> 00:25:01,831
We're going to have a long gossip session tonight.

362
00:25:04,075 --> 00:25:05,488
Here, this one's better.

363
00:25:06,635 --> 00:25:08,293
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

364
00:25:09,084 --> 00:25:11,751
- Can you reach it, honey?
- Thank you.

365
00:27:22,933 --> 00:27:23,924
Hey.

366
00:27:25,244 --> 00:27:26,320
Hey.

367
00:27:54,755 --> 00:27:57,457
What a relief. Exams are finally over.

368
00:27:59,213 --> 00:28:00,893
But we still have the football tournament.

369
00:28:01,982 --> 00:28:03,600
Time really flies, huh?

370
00:28:03,982 --> 00:28:05,626
We'll be in Grade 11 soon.

371
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:11,580
And I'm turning 17 soon.
I'll be 17 before you.

372
00:28:12,195 --> 00:28:15,324
You should start calling me big brother.

373
00:28:16,604 --> 00:28:18,660
You're only two months older than me and want me to call you that?

374
00:28:19,062 --> 00:28:21,333
I'm seven years younger than Singha and I still don't call him that.

375
00:28:22,262 --> 00:28:24,884
By the way, about your brother...

376
00:28:25,613 --> 00:28:27,160
Aren't you going to talk to him?

377
00:28:28,782 --> 00:28:31,880
- Talk about what?
- Just... have a proper conversation.

378
00:28:33,657 --> 00:28:36,120
I'd rather die than try talking nicely to him.

379
00:28:37,315 --> 00:28:38,533
Why?

380
00:28:38,951 --> 00:28:41,186
- Just once.
- No.

381
00:28:42,195 --> 00:28:45,573
Just once. Invite him to dinner or something. I'll come too.

382
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:49,013
- You'll come too?
- Yeah.

383
00:28:49,408 --> 00:28:51,800
I'll sit there and be nosy. So you won't feel awkward.

384
00:28:54,408 --> 00:28:56,480
I don't even know if he'll show up.

385
00:28:56,660 --> 00:28:59,706
You have to try. He even showed up for the parent-teacher meeting.

386
00:29:00,711 --> 00:29:01,866
True.

387
00:29:04,870 --> 00:29:06,848
- But you have to come with me.
- Easy.

388
00:29:08,528 --> 00:29:10,582
Even though your brother looks scary.

389
00:29:12,488 --> 00:29:13,582
Where should I arrange to meet him?

390
00:29:15,222 --> 00:29:16,880
Leave that to me.

391
00:29:20,986 --> 00:29:22,977
(My N'Suer)

392
00:29:38,311 --> 00:29:39,391
What's up?

393
00:29:40,773 --> 00:29:41,740
Singha.

394
00:29:43,404 --> 00:29:44,413
You...

395
00:29:45,008 --> 00:29:46,488
today—

396
00:29:47,177 --> 00:29:49,782
Actually, have you been free lately?

397
00:29:50,097 --> 00:29:52,297
Anytime. When are you free?

398
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:56,546
What is it?

399
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:01,475
I need to talk to you about something.

400
00:30:02,257 --> 00:30:03,502
Something serious.

401
00:30:09,582 --> 00:30:10,444
Mm.

402
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:12,666
Just set it up.

403
00:30:13,053 --> 00:30:14,528
I'll send you the location.

404
00:30:17,466 --> 00:30:18,288
Yeah.

405
00:30:32,568 --> 00:30:33,360
Ben.

406
00:30:34,293 --> 00:30:35,213
This is serious.

407
00:30:35,866 --> 00:30:37,448
Get over here right now.

408
00:30:39,982 --> 00:30:41,244
Meet me here.

409
00:30:49,853 --> 00:30:50,568
Singha.

410
00:30:51,786 --> 00:30:52,568
What's up?

411
00:30:52,675 --> 00:30:55,355
The place you sent me is right, isn't it?

412
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:57,542
Suer sent me this place.

413
00:31:05,244 --> 00:31:06,542
Wrong place?

414
00:31:07,142 --> 00:31:08,871
No, it's right.

415
00:31:09,675 --> 00:31:12,946
I should be asking if your brother pinned the right location.

416
00:31:15,217 --> 00:31:16,720
I don't think it's wrong.

417
00:31:18,702 --> 00:31:19,506
Let's go.

418
00:31:57,413 --> 00:31:59,240
Hey, your brother's here.

419
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,386
Duennao?

420
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,340
Yes, it's me.

421
00:32:37,795 --> 00:32:40,253
Uh, have you ordered anything yet?

422
00:32:42,173 --> 00:32:42,924
Not yet.

423
00:32:45,742 --> 00:32:47,940
Then let me recommend our new menu item.

424
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,333
The melon bingsu is really good.

425
00:32:51,860 --> 00:32:53,408
The smoothies here are great too.

426
00:33:03,208 --> 00:33:05,995
- Does your brother drink smoothies?
- How would I know?

427
00:33:08,484 --> 00:33:11,080
- Then ask him.
- You ask him.

428
00:33:11,408 --> 00:33:13,693
Suer, you ask.

429
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:14,964
What did we agree on?

430
00:33:22,306 --> 00:33:23,337
Hey.

431
00:33:23,622 --> 00:33:24,871
Do you drink smoothies?

432
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:29,951
Yeah.

433
00:33:30,617 --> 00:33:32,013
Order whatever you want.

434
00:33:50,906 --> 00:33:52,857
What did you want to say?

435
00:33:58,111 --> 00:33:59,342
Your brother's talking to you.

436
00:33:59,737 --> 00:34:02,355
- I know.
- Then answer him.

437
00:34:08,857 --> 00:34:10,260
I don't like you.

438
00:34:12,220 --> 00:34:13,333
So?

439
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:17,146
Suer.

440
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,755
How are you supposed to talk like that?

441
00:34:20,408 --> 00:34:21,524
What did I tell you?

442
00:34:30,208 --> 00:34:31,662
Okay.

443
00:34:33,582 --> 00:34:35,488
This is the only time

444
00:34:35,817 --> 00:34:38,777
I'm going to talk to you seriously.

445
00:34:39,471 --> 00:34:40,706
No bias.

446
00:34:41,075 --> 00:34:42,613
No emotions.

447
00:34:43,702 --> 00:34:45,600
But if we still can't understand each other after this,

448
00:34:46,342 --> 00:34:48,764
I'm done talking.

449
00:34:50,906 --> 00:34:51,822
I...

450
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:59,644
don't like the way you talk to me.

451
00:35:05,088 --> 00:35:09,146
Why are you laughing?
See? You always look down on me.

452
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:12,071
Come on, Nao. Let's go.
We shouldn't have come.

453
00:35:12,342 --> 00:35:13,560
No, that's not it.

454
00:35:19,475 --> 00:35:21,413
Well.

455
00:35:21,871 --> 00:35:23,484
I'll wait for you over there.

456
00:35:30,951 --> 00:35:31,933
Why?

457
00:35:37,235 --> 00:35:38,604
Because I don't like it.

458
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:43,493
I want us to get along.

459
00:35:44,124 --> 00:35:45,688
Sometimes,

460
00:35:45,955 --> 00:35:47,982
there's no reason for us to fight at all.

461
00:35:48,946 --> 00:35:50,768
But you're always messing with me.

462
00:35:52,093 --> 00:35:53,951
Or do you dislike me so much that...

463
00:35:54,213 --> 00:35:56,302
- you can't even talk to me nicely?
- What about you?

464
00:35:57,004 --> 00:35:58,060
Do you hate me?

465
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:05,555
I don't hate you.

466
00:36:07,297 --> 00:36:08,466
I just...

467
00:36:09,133 --> 00:36:11,004
don't like what you've done to me.

468
00:36:15,951 --> 00:36:16,880
Okay.

469
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:22,391
From now on, I won't speak badly to you anymore.

470
00:36:23,866 --> 00:36:25,500
Is that all you wanted to say?

471
00:36:28,008 --> 00:36:29,111
One more thing.

472
00:36:34,075 --> 00:36:35,720
I've decided.

473
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:39,471
I'm going to work with our family.

474
00:36:44,835 --> 00:36:46,604
Didn't you tell me

475
00:36:47,444 --> 00:36:50,400
that I shouldn't have friends or people I care about?

476
00:36:52,346 --> 00:36:53,542
Because they...

477
00:36:54,053 --> 00:36:55,346
would be in danger.

478
00:36:56,928 --> 00:36:58,511
But I've made up my mind.

479
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:03,133
I don't want to lose anyone.

480
00:37:05,137 --> 00:37:06,795
I'll protect everyone myself.

481
00:37:16,133 --> 00:37:17,551
You've made your decision?

482
00:37:23,524 --> 00:37:24,706
One more thing.

483
00:37:27,031 --> 00:37:28,826
I'm entrusting my people to you.

484
00:37:30,008 --> 00:37:31,577
Keep them safe.

485
00:37:32,337 --> 00:37:33,688
Because right now,

486
00:37:34,100 --> 00:37:35,497
there's nothing I can do.

487
00:37:38,102 --> 00:37:39,235
I understand.

488
00:37:43,900 --> 00:37:45,022
Thank you.

489
00:37:46,462 --> 00:37:47,391
Mm.

490
00:37:47,946 --> 00:37:50,173
I should get going. I've got something to do.

491
00:37:50,924 --> 00:37:51,933
Wait.

492
00:37:59,155 --> 00:38:00,417
I have a football match tomorrow.

493
00:38:02,813 --> 00:38:04,173
I'm the captain too.

494
00:38:09,191 --> 00:38:10,666
If you're free, come by.

495
00:38:39,013 --> 00:38:39,955
How did it go?

496
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:44,448
Nothing much.

497
00:39:00,742 --> 00:39:02,880
Singha, stop crying already.

498
00:39:06,533 --> 00:39:07,560
Ben.

499
00:39:08,577 --> 00:39:09,768
My little brother...

500
00:39:11,408 --> 00:39:12,408
Suer...

501
00:39:12,848 --> 00:39:14,302
Has he grown up that much already?

502
00:39:15,066 --> 00:39:17,182
Yeah. People grow up with time.

503
00:39:17,640 --> 00:39:19,342
No, that's not it.

504
00:39:20,053 --> 00:39:21,871
Earlier, he wouldn't listen to anyone.

505
00:39:23,195 --> 00:39:24,866
He wouldn't listen to anybody.

506
00:39:26,155 --> 00:39:27,820
But now he's telling me

507
00:39:28,088 --> 00:39:29,780
he wants to work with me.

508
00:39:30,751 --> 00:39:32,306
Because he wants to protect others.

509
00:39:35,542 --> 00:39:37,777
And he even thanked me.

510
00:39:39,351 --> 00:39:40,968
It's good that you two talked things out.

511
00:39:42,746 --> 00:39:43,644
So,

512
00:39:44,706 --> 00:39:47,035
what about that gang leader kid?

513
00:39:47,342 --> 00:39:48,577
How's he doing?

514
00:39:49,613 --> 00:39:51,200
Anything unusual?

515
00:39:54,248 --> 00:39:55,511
No.

516
00:39:56,817 --> 00:39:57,822
Nope.

517
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,711
I don't know.

518
00:40:04,710 --> 00:40:06,013
You're useless.

519
00:41:39,817 --> 00:41:40,937
What do you guys think?

520
00:41:41,244 --> 00:41:42,720
What should I do next?

521
00:41:43,973 --> 00:41:46,195
Do you want him to know that you like him?

522
00:41:48,662 --> 00:41:49,546
I...

523
00:41:50,151 --> 00:41:53,684
I want him to know, and I want him to feel the same way.

524
00:41:54,057 --> 00:41:55,928
But I don't know if he does.

525
00:41:59,075 --> 00:42:03,555
Well, if you ask me, there are several possibilities.

526
00:42:04,008 --> 00:42:04,986
First,

527
00:42:05,426 --> 00:42:08,580
he might already know you like him, and he likes you too,

528
00:42:08,986 --> 00:42:10,120
but he's too scared to say it.

529
00:42:10,715 --> 00:42:14,911
Second, if Nao knows, he might open his heart to you.

530
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:17,031
But third,

531
00:42:17,568 --> 00:42:19,746
Nao knows that you like him,

532
00:42:20,128 --> 00:42:22,582
but he doesn't feel the same and would rather stay friends.

533
00:42:22,773 --> 00:42:24,053
Or fourth,

534
00:42:25,262 --> 00:42:28,742
he knows you like him, but he's not okay with it.

535
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,417
Once he finds out,

536
00:42:32,017 --> 00:42:33,662
he cuts you out of his life.

537
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,248
Shit.

538
00:42:36,711 --> 00:42:39,253
I don't think Nao would be that cruel.

539
00:42:40,088 --> 00:42:41,631
I don't think it's number four.

540
00:42:41,900 --> 00:42:44,973
At worst, it'd be number three.

541
00:42:45,573 --> 00:42:46,880
Better as friends.

542
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:49,617
Would that really be okay?

543
00:42:53,804 --> 00:42:56,022
Damn it, I don't want to be just friends.

544
00:42:56,617 --> 00:43:00,564
Can you really be friends with someone you want to see, want to talk to,

545
00:43:00,848 --> 00:43:03,822
want to take care of, and want to prioritize?

546
00:43:04,871 --> 00:43:06,951
And I want to be important to him too.

547
00:43:07,666 --> 00:43:09,284
Friends don't feel like that, do they?

548
00:43:15,924 --> 00:43:16,871
What are you listening to?

549
00:43:19,302 --> 00:43:20,751
Hey, why'd you stop it?

550
00:43:21,551 --> 00:43:22,720
What?

551
00:43:24,102 --> 00:43:26,435
What is it? "Friend (Doesn't) Love."

552
00:43:26,857 --> 00:43:28,182
You listen to this song too?

553
00:43:29,537 --> 00:43:32,066
Mick sent it to me.

554
00:43:32,977 --> 00:43:34,626
Really?

555
00:43:36,568 --> 00:43:38,600
So you've fallen in love these days?

556
00:43:39,506 --> 00:43:42,142
- Mick just...
- Answer me right now.

557
00:43:42,893 --> 00:43:44,440
Mick really sent it to me.

558
00:43:45,471 --> 00:43:47,186
You're acting suspicious.

559
00:43:48,617 --> 00:43:51,822
Come on, tell me. I won't tell anyone. You can trust me.

560
00:43:52,213 --> 00:43:55,471
Hey, I said there's nothing, so there's nothing.

561
00:43:57,555 --> 00:43:59,400
Come on, let me listen then.

562
00:44:00,688 --> 00:44:02,133
Just listen to it.

563
00:44:04,097 --> 00:44:05,391
Give me one side.

564
00:44:09,106 --> 00:44:12,884
It's just a song. Nothing special.

565
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:37,995
Nao.

566
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:39,540
Hm?

567
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:43,911
If someone confessed to you, what would you do?

568
00:44:46,364 --> 00:44:47,324
That won't happen.

569
00:44:48,568 --> 00:44:50,080
Just hypothetically.

570
00:44:51,515 --> 00:44:52,662
I guess I'd...

571
00:44:53,217 --> 00:44:54,284
turn them down.

572
00:45:04,360 --> 00:45:06,862
Right now, I'm not thinking about having a relationship.

573
00:45:07,164 --> 00:45:09,471
I can barely handle my own life.

574
00:45:13,057 --> 00:45:14,640
And if not now,

575
00:45:15,182 --> 00:45:16,208
then when?

576
00:45:18,520 --> 00:45:19,497
I don't know.

577
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:24,968
Why are you asking so many questions? Gathering intel?

578
00:45:25,471 --> 00:45:26,920
Didn't you say you didn't like anyone?

579
00:45:28,706 --> 00:45:31,942
Aha! Suer!

580
00:45:34,333 --> 00:45:36,493
- No.
- I'm not teasing you anymore.

581
00:45:36,906 --> 00:45:37,844
Just kidding.

582
00:45:40,986 --> 00:45:43,875
Give me that. By the way,

583
00:45:44,297 --> 00:45:45,951
what are you doing out this late?

584
00:45:47,342 --> 00:45:48,733
I couldn't sleep.

585
00:45:48,982 --> 00:45:53,262
Thought I'd go for a walk and get some fresh air, but then I saw you sitting here acting like you're in a music video.

586
00:45:56,186 --> 00:45:57,315
Want to go for a ride?

587
00:46:01,160 --> 00:46:02,226
Let me grab a jacket.

588
00:46:09,324 --> 00:46:10,622
Friend (Doesn't) Love?

589
00:46:14,853 --> 00:46:16,724
So? Feeling better?

590
00:46:19,500 --> 00:46:20,551
A little.

591
00:46:22,733 --> 00:46:24,040
The weather's nice.

592
00:46:28,408 --> 00:46:30,720
Aren't you nervous at all?

593
00:46:32,426 --> 00:46:33,648
Not really.

594
00:46:34,493 --> 00:46:36,657
Even though it's my first time, I'm not nervous.

595
00:46:37,577 --> 00:46:40,444
- I don't know why.
- So you think you're gonna win?

596
00:46:41,060 --> 00:46:42,688
That confident, huh?

597
00:46:44,853 --> 00:46:46,026
Something like that.

598
00:46:47,173 --> 00:46:48,804
I think I have to win.

599
00:46:49,622 --> 00:46:51,080
This time too.

600
00:46:54,382 --> 00:46:59,346
Hey, don't put so much pressure on yourself. Football isn't a one-man game.

601
00:47:01,160 --> 00:47:02,306
Yeah.

602
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:03,795
True.

603
00:47:04,511 --> 00:47:07,200
But the other team is insanely good, right?

604
00:47:09,831 --> 00:47:13,800
You know what we have that they don't?

605
00:47:16,702 --> 00:47:17,528
What?

606
00:47:18,751 --> 00:47:19,684
Me.

607
00:47:22,391 --> 00:47:23,666
Suer.

608
00:47:25,342 --> 00:47:29,635
- That's exactly what's making me even more stressed.
- Asshole.

609
00:47:35,111 --> 00:47:36,315
Suer.

610
00:47:37,008 --> 00:47:42,142
I bragged to my mom I'd score two goals.
Make sure you pass me the ball.

611
00:47:42,848 --> 00:47:44,502
Don't I always?

612
00:47:48,813 --> 00:47:49,475
Okay.

613
00:47:54,311 --> 00:47:55,693
Suer.

614
00:47:56,031 --> 00:48:00,475
- Do you think we'll win?
- I told you, we'll win. You've got me on your team.

615
00:48:01,420 --> 00:48:05,008
Everyone else has been training together too.
What are you worried about?

616
00:48:07,300 --> 00:48:10,688
If we win, we win together. If we lose, we lose together.

617
00:48:11,097 --> 00:48:12,102
That's all.

618
00:48:17,497 --> 00:48:18,506
Yeah.

619
00:48:19,142 --> 00:48:20,546
Win together.

620
00:48:27,977 --> 00:48:29,337
You're such a scaredy-cat.

621
00:48:40,684 --> 00:48:42,100
This field is huge.

622
00:48:46,346 --> 00:48:47,746
Holy shit.

623
00:48:48,106 --> 00:48:49,880
There are so many people.

624
00:48:50,302 --> 00:48:52,644
Yeah. I was fine before.

625
00:48:52,942 --> 00:48:54,337
Now I'm getting nervous.

626
00:48:55,262 --> 00:48:57,782
Yeah, you're making me nervous too.

627
00:48:58,595 --> 00:49:00,333
Come on. Coach will call us soon.

628
00:49:02,088 --> 00:49:02,897
Let's go.

629
00:49:07,080 --> 00:49:09,222
The Provincial Youth Football Qualifiers.

630
00:49:14,200 --> 00:49:15,893
Come up here. Where are the seats?

631
00:49:20,742 --> 00:49:23,151
Dan, where's Duen?

632
00:49:23,524 --> 00:49:24,880
I can't see him.

633
00:49:32,075 --> 00:49:34,395
There he is, Mom. He just arrived.

634
00:49:35,088 --> 00:49:36,320
Duen!

635
00:49:38,422 --> 00:49:39,906
Mom's over here!

636
00:49:55,831 --> 00:49:57,484
Go, Duen!

637
00:50:18,204 --> 00:50:19,546
Go, Duen!

638
00:50:29,826 --> 00:50:31,777
Great job, son!

639
00:51:33,804 --> 00:51:35,960
Duen's team is ahead, Mom. There's still a chance.

640
00:51:43,844 --> 00:51:45,120
Come on!

641
00:52:17,986 --> 00:52:22,600
- Great job, Duen! Great job!
- You're amazing, Duen!

642
00:52:34,560 --> 00:52:37,004
- They won, Mom!
- Really?

643
00:52:41,457 --> 00:52:43,755
One, two, three, yay!

644
00:52:48,324 --> 00:52:51,977
We won! Yay!

645
00:52:52,875 --> 00:52:54,780
Amazing!

646
00:53:21,520 --> 00:53:22,728
Let's go.

647
00:53:35,466 --> 00:53:40,711
See? I told you, man. We're awesome. We're freaking amazing.

648
00:53:41,546 --> 00:53:42,780
Man...

649
00:53:43,195 --> 00:53:44,724
You did great, Nao.

650
00:53:44,955 --> 00:53:46,613
I'm exhausted.

651
00:53:48,680 --> 00:53:50,780
- What's up?
- Huh?

652
00:53:52,004 --> 00:53:53,431
Tired.

653
00:53:54,604 --> 00:53:58,257
Hey, I'm gonna go see Singha first.
Just for a bit. He's leaving soon.

654
00:53:59,964 --> 00:54:00,951
Okay.

655
00:54:01,364 --> 00:54:02,306
Be nice.

656
00:54:29,644 --> 00:54:31,448
- Duen!
- Let go!

657
00:54:31,537 --> 00:54:32,537
- Let go, damn it!
- Let me go!

658
00:54:32,591 --> 00:54:33,724
Dan, what's wrong?

659
00:54:34,693 --> 00:54:35,924
What's happening?

660
00:54:37,940 --> 00:54:39,288
- Let go!
- Why are you grabbing us? Let go!

661
00:54:39,328 --> 00:54:40,857
Mom! Dan!

662
00:54:40,991 --> 00:54:43,248
Duen, help!

663
00:54:43,373 --> 00:54:45,280
Help Mom!

664
00:54:54,315 --> 00:54:55,266
Chat!

665
00:54:56,271 --> 00:54:57,142
Let go!

666
00:54:57,408 --> 00:54:58,466
You bastard!

667
00:54:59,315 --> 00:55:01,026
Long time no see.

668
00:55:02,008 --> 00:55:03,404
Still got a big mouth, huh?

669
00:55:03,791 --> 00:55:05,133
You scumbag.

670
00:55:05,986 --> 00:55:07,764
Get them in the car.

671
00:55:08,088 --> 00:55:09,511
- Hurry up.
- Duen!

672
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:12,780
- Let go!
- Duen!

673
00:55:12,920 --> 00:55:14,560
- Duen!
- Move!

674
00:55:23,413 --> 00:55:26,662
Help! Somebody help!
Why are you following me?

675
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:29,484
Relax, Nao. It's me.

676
00:55:29,951 --> 00:55:32,071
- Ow!
- Tiger.

677
00:55:32,173 --> 00:55:33,320
I've missed you.

678
00:55:33,537 --> 00:55:35,231
So? Wanna move to Chiang Mai with me?

679
00:55:35,346 --> 00:55:37,435
Sure. North or south, I'll go anywhere.

680
00:55:37,564 --> 00:55:38,631
You two are glued together.

681
00:55:38,780 --> 00:55:40,546
We're best friends, that's why.

682
00:55:40,742 --> 00:55:42,200
Right, buddy?

683
00:55:42,613 --> 00:55:44,506
So, what's up with that girl?

684
00:55:44,933 --> 00:55:47,360
I think I'll give her a chance. She's pretty cute.

685
00:55:47,542 --> 00:55:48,520
Come on, let's get some barbecue.

686
00:55:48,617 --> 00:55:49,795
What about me, Nao?

687
00:55:50,186 --> 00:55:51,537
I like you too.
